# Data lake Parquet (read path only)

Upload / ETL tooling for Becker archives is **not** in this repo. This rule covers how the **Lychee app** reads Parquet.

## Server proxy (private bucket)

- **Route**: `src/pages/api/data-lake/parquet.js` — server **`GetObject`**; browser calls same-origin with `?path=relative/to/prefix/file.parquet`.
- **Polymarket prefix**: `DATA_LAKE_S3_KEY_PREFIX` (e.g. ends with `…/polymarket`).
- **Kalshi prefix**: `DATA_LAKE_KALSHI_S3_KEY_PREFIX` **or** derive by replacing trailing `/polymarket` with `/kalshi` on the polymarket prefix.
- **Dataset switch**: `?lake=kalshi` uses the Kalshi prefix; default uses the polymarket prefix.
- **Client**: `NEXT_PUBLIC_DATA_LAKE_USE_S3_PROXY=true` plus bucket/region/AWS credentials on the server (see env docs in the API file).

## Athena (lake SQL)

- **Routes**: `athena-query.js` (sync POST), `athena-query/start.js` (POST → id), `athena-query/status.js` (GET poll + rows when done). Bounded `SELECT` only; table names mapped server-side.
- **Historical UI samples**: `DataLakeParquetPanel` → start + status poll via `fetchAthenaSample.js` → `ingestAthenaResultAsView` in `duckdbWasmClient.js`.

## Public HTTPS (optional)

If Parquet is served from a public bucket URL, other flows can use `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` base URL envs — helpers remain in `src/config/dataLakeParquetSamples.js`.

## Security

- **Never commit real AWS keys.** Server-side env only for the proxy.
- **CORS** on the bucket matters when the **browser** fetches Parquet via **public HTTPS URLs** (not via the proxy).
